%description
This module recognizes the above date/time formats. Usually a date and
a time are specified. There are numerous options for controlling what is
recognized and what is not.  The return code is always the time in seconds
since January 1st, 1970 or undef if it was unable to parse the time.  If a
timezone is specified it must be after the time. Year specifications can
be tacked onto the end of absolute times.  If parsedate() is called from
array context, then it will return two elements. On sucessful parses,
it will return the seconds and what remains of its input string. On
unsucessful parses, it will return undef and an error string.

